{"id": 66, "ts": 1778840393.8649502, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_3", "message": "I\u2019ve now gathered the missing piece on Candidate\u202fD: he **takes responsibility seriously**, which gives us a concrete indication of reliability. However, we still have **no information on his calmness under pressure**, and the existing negatives \u2013 hot temper, moody, loner, and know\u2011it\u2011all perception \u2013 suggest potential crew\u2011interaction problems that could be amplified on long\u2011haul flights.\nComparing the four candidates with all available data:\n- **Candidate\u202fB** excels on reliability (100\u202f% reliable) and calmness in crises, and has strong technical skills (weather assessment, computer proficiency). Yet the documented **weak memory for numbers** directly threatens in\u2011flight calculations, and his **nasty remarks and wrong tone** pose a clear risk to crew cohesion over extended missions.\n- **Candidate\u202fC** demonstrates rapid, correct decision\u2011making, excellent stress resilience, and, crucially, **creates a positive atmosphere with his crew**. These traits support both safety and long\u2011duration crew coordination. His downsides \u2013 difficulty communicating ideas, an egocentric reputation, and limited interest in further education \u2013 are important but do not directly compromise immediate safety or reliability.\n- **Candidate\u202fA** shows strong situational awareness and leadership but lacks any evidence of reliability, calmness under pressure, or crew\u2011interaction skills, and his unfriendly attitude and unhealthy habits raise additional concerns.\n- **Candidate\u202fD** is reliable (takes responsibility seriously) and strong in problem\u2011solving and concentration, yet the absence of calmness data and the presence of a hot temper, moodiness, and a loner image make him a risky choice for the collaborative, high\u2011stress environment of long\u2011distance flights.\nGiven the core criteria\u2014reliability, calmness, technical competence, and especially crew cooperation\u2014the balance tips toward **Candidate\u202fC**. He offers the most well\u2011rounded profile for safe, sustained international operations, with the only remaining concerns being communication style and long\u2011term development, which are less safety\u2011critical than B\u2019s memory weakness or D\u2019s temperament issues.\n**My vote:** Candidate\u202fC\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}"}
